/*
========================================================
PENDING INTENT – INTUITIVE + ANDROID-LEVEL EXPLANATION
========================================================

--------------------------------------------------------
WHAT IS PendingIntent (IN SIMPLE WORDS)
--------------------------------------------------------
PendingIntent is a special object that gives
the Android SYSTEM permission to execute
your Intent later on your app’s behalf.

--------------------------------------------------------
THE “PERMISSION SLIP” ANALOGY (IMPORTANT)
--------------------------------------------------------
Think of PendingIntent like a signed slip saying:

"Dear Android,
If my app is not running or is killed,
you are ALLOWED to perform this action
for me later."

--------------------------------------------------------
WHY ANDROID NEEDS THIS SLIP
--------------------------------------------------------
• Your app process may be dead
• System cannot trust normal Intent
• Android must have explicit permission
• Security & lifecycle safety

--------------------------------------------------------
NORMAL Intent vs PendingIntent
--------------------------------------------------------
Intent:
• Owned by your app
• Works immediately
• Fails if app is killed

PendingIntent:
• Owned by Android system
• Can be executed later
• Survives app death
• Can wake your app

--------------------------------------------------------
WHAT ANDROID DOES INTERNALLY
--------------------------------------------------------
• Android stores the PendingIntent
• Android remembers:
   - What to do
   - Which app owns it
   - What permissions it has
• At trigger time, Android executes it
  as if YOUR app requested it

--------------------------------------------------------
WHY PendingIntent IS REQUIRED FOR:
--------------------------------------------------------
• AlarmManager
• Notification clicks
• App widgets
• System callbacks

--------------------------------------------------------
HOW ANDROID EXECUTES IT
--------------------------------------------------------
AlarmManager fires →
Android checks PendingIntent →
Android temporarily assumes your app’s identity →
Android performs the Intent

--------------------------------------------------------
SECURITY BENEFIT
--------------------------------------------------------
• Prevents other apps from modifying your intent
• Controlled execution
• Requires explicit flags (IMMUTABLE / MUTABLE)

--------------------------------------------------------
ANDROID 12+ SECURITY NOTE
--------------------------------------------------------
PendingIntent must specify:
• FLAG_IMMUTABLE (recommended)
• FLAG_MUTABLE (only when needed)

--------------------------------------------------------
REAL-WORLD ANALOGY (BEST ONE)
--------------------------------------------------------
PendingIntent =
"Pre-approved instruction card"
stored with Android system,
used later when conditions are met.

--------------------------------------------------------
ONE-LINE TAKEAWAY (MEMORIZE)
--------------------------------------------------------
PendingIntent is Android’s trusted
permission slip that allows the system
to safely run your Intent later,
even if your app is not alive.
========================================================
*/
